00:30:41.989 --> 00:30:44.170
little sphere 4/3Π
little r cubed,

00:30:44.170 --> 00:30:47.068
and all I'm saying is forget
these 4 thirds pis.

00:30:47.068 --> 00:30:53.029
It's just little r^(3)
over big R^(3).

00:30:53.029 --> 00:30:56.950
Therefore, the electric field
now, E(r),

00:30:56.950 --> 00:31:03.330
looks like Q over
4Πε

00:31:03.330 --> 00:31:10.180
_0r divided by
r^(3).

00:31:10.180 --> 00:31:14.680
This is for r &lt;
R,

00:31:14.680 --> 00:31:18.665
is equal to Q/4Π
ε_0

00:31:18.665 --> 00:31:22.561
(1/r^(2)) for
r &gt;

00:31:22.561 --> 00:31:23.740
R.
 

00:31:23.740 --> 00:31:27.990
Student:  Isn't it
