00:45:25.949 --> 00:45:31.074
By the way, I should tell you
that Gauss's Law--let me do this

00:45:31.074 --> 00:45:32.250
one example.
 

00:45:32.250 --> 00:45:34.360
I'll tell you what the
restriction of Gauss's Law is.

00:45:34.360 --> 00:45:38.782
So we come to this problem and
we can again argue by symmetry

00:45:38.782 --> 00:45:42.909
the field lines have to be
radially away from the axis of

00:45:42.909 --> 00:45:46.311
their line,
and if you look at it from the

00:45:46.311 --> 00:45:51.934
edge,
from one edge it'll look like

00:45:51.934 --> 00:45:52.989
this.
 

00:45:52.989 --> 00:45:55.244
If you look at the wire from
the edge the lines should be

00:45:55.244 --> 00:45:56.130
going out like that.
 

00:45:56.130 --> 00:45:57.980
It's like a hedgehog but it's
cylindrical.

00:45:57.980 --> 00:45:59.619
It's not in all three
dimensions.

00:45:59.619 --> 00:46:03.369
It's radial in this direction.
 

00:46:03.369 --> 00:46:06.713
And the question is and the
field has to be constant along

00:46:06.713 --> 00:46:09.998
the length of the infinite wire
at each point at the same

00:46:09.998 --> 00:46:13.635
distance because if you move the
wire horizontally it looks the

00:46:13.635 --> 00:46:16.510
same so the field distribution
cannot vary.

00:46:16.510 --> 00:46:19.750
If it is a finite wire you
cannot make the argument.

00:46:19.750 --> 00:46:23.614
In a finite wire as you come
near the edges lines will start

00:46:23.614 --> 00:46:24.268
tilting.
 

00:46:24.268 --> 00:46:27.320
But a finite wire doesn't look
the same when you move it;

00:46:27.320 --> 00:46:29.099
an infinite wire does.
 

00:46:29.099 --> 00:46:32.485
Therefore, for an infinite wire
if you don't stop here the lines

00:46:32.485 --> 00:46:35.496
will always look the same,
so that if you shift them over

00:46:35.496 --> 00:46:37.110
they should look the same.
 

00:46:37.110 --> 00:46:41.858
So the only unknown question is
- I know the field is in this

00:46:41.858 --> 00:46:46.608
direction radially away from the
wire in all directions whose

00:46:46.608 --> 00:46:50.329
magnitude is fixed at a distance
r,

00:46:50.329 --> 00:46:53.590
but I want to know what the
magnitude is.

00:46:53.590 --> 00:46:57.597
Again, I'm going to take
Gauss's Law and I'm going to

00:46:57.597 --> 00:47:00.139
apply to the following surface.
 

00:47:00.139 --> 00:47:08.561
Surface is a cylinder and the
cylinder has some length

00:47:08.561 --> 00:47:11.726
l,
and it's got some radius

00:47:11.726 --> 00:47:14.820
r and the flat faces of
the cylinder are parallel,

00:47:14.820 --> 00:47:29.927
so if you really want to give
the nice picture here they look

00:47:29.927 --> 00:47:32.949
like this.
 

00:47:32.949 --> 00:47:35.619
So Gauss's Law can be applied
only to a closed surface.

00:47:35.619 --> 00:47:36.768
You understand that?
 

00:47:36.768 --> 00:47:40.248
You cannot do it for an open
surface because only if you trap

00:47:40.248 --> 00:47:43.668
the charge completely in all
directions will you count every

00:47:43.668 --> 00:47:44.190
line.
 

00:47:44.190 --> 00:47:46.902
If you've got holes in your
surface then stuff can escape

00:47:46.902 --> 00:47:48.550
and you cannot promise anything.
 

00:47:48.550 --> 00:47:52.661
So I need a closed surface and
my closed surface is the

00:47:52.661 --> 00:47:53.500
cylinder.
 

00:47:53.500 --> 00:47:56.115
So I'm going to write,
once again, the surface

00:47:56.115 --> 00:47:59.603
integral of the electric field
on that cylinder is the charge

00:47:59.603 --> 00:48:00.360
enclosed.
 

00:48:00.360 --> 00:48:03.150
The charge enclosed is the
easiest part.

00:48:03.150 --> 00:48:06.260
I'm going to give you 10
seconds to think in your head.

00:48:06.260 --> 00:48:11.480
What is a charge enclosed by
the cylinder?

00:48:11.480 --> 00:48:12.789
Okay?
 

00:48:12.789 --> 00:48:16.063
It's charge per unit length
times the length of wire trapped

00:48:16.063 --> 00:48:20.548
inside the cylinder and then,
of course, I have this

00:48:20.548 --> 00:48:24.489
1/ε_0.
 

00:48:24.489 --> 00:48:27.530
It still is a statement about
the integral of E on the

00:48:27.530 --> 00:48:30.519
surface, and it could be any
surface, but the beauty of this

00:48:30.519 --> 00:48:31.989
surface is the following.
 

00:48:31.989 --> 00:48:34.806
There are contributions to
E⋅dA from

00:48:34.806 --> 00:48:38.280
the curvy side of the cylinder
and from the flat side.

00:48:38.280 --> 00:48:42.373
In the flat side the surface
vector, area vector dA

00:48:42.373 --> 00:48:46.179
for any small portion,
or in fact for the entire face,

00:48:46.179 --> 00:48:47.400
is like that.
 

00:48:47.400 --> 00:48:52.780
The electric field runs along
that face so the dot product is

00:48:52.780 --> 00:48:53.139
0.
 

00:48:53.139 --> 00:48:58.333
So I got 0 from the left side,
0 from the right side,

00:48:58.333 --> 00:49:02.929
then I got non-zero from the
curvy cylinder.

00:49:02.929 --> 00:49:07.570
On the curved cylinder you can,
I hope, see that every area

00:49:07.570 --> 00:49:11.489
vector is actually parallel to
the field lines.

00:49:11.489 --> 00:49:16.628
So just like on a sphere this
integral will be E(r) times the

00:49:16.628 --> 00:49:21.679
surface of the curvy part of the
cylinder which is 2Πr

00:49:21.679 --> 00:49:23.650
times L.
 

00:49:23.650 --> 00:49:27.489
That's the area of the curved
part of the cylinder.

00:49:27.489 --> 00:49:30.300
So you see L cancels
out, and it better cancel out

00:49:30.300 --> 00:49:32.760
because L is an
artificial construction.

00:49:32.760 --> 00:49:34.768
We made up L.
 

00:49:34.768 --> 00:49:37.380
The answer should not depend on
the Gaussian surface you picked.

00:49:37.380 --> 00:49:40.050
I told you it's a figment of
our imagination,

00:49:40.050 --> 00:49:44.753
so it doesn't depend on it,
and we find E(r)

00:49:44.753 --> 00:49:48.880
= λ/2Πε
_0r,

00:49:48.880 --> 00:49:52.885
which is the result we got
earlier on by doing all the

00:49:52.885 --> 00:49:54.849
brute force integration.
 

00:49:54.849 --> 00:49:57.550
Remember we took a point here.
 

00:49:57.550 --> 00:49:58.530
We took some segment.
 

00:49:58.530 --> 00:50:01.637
We drew the arrows,
did the integrals,

00:50:01.637 --> 00:50:05.922
sine thetas and whatnot,
but you can get that in one

00:50:05.922 --> 00:50:06.679
shot.
 

00:50:06.679 --> 00:50:10.313
So it looks like Gauss's Law is
the easy way to do stuff,

00:50:10.313 --> 00:50:13.621
and you may wonder why we
bother to do any difficult

00:50:13.621 --> 00:50:14.530
integrals.
 

00:50:14.530 --> 00:50:19.152
The reason is that if I change
the symmetry of the problem in

00:50:19.152 --> 00:50:22.929
the slightest way I cannot
calculate the field.

00:50:22.929 --> 00:50:26.476
For example,
if on the spherical charge

00:50:26.476 --> 00:50:31.891
distribution instead of a sphere
I made a little blip here,

00:50:31.891 --> 00:50:36.840
maybe did a little surgery and
put that guy here.

00:50:36.840 --> 00:50:39.260
We're dead.
 

00:50:39.260 --> 00:50:41.724
I mean, there's a formula for
the field, but no one can

00:50:41.724 --> 00:50:43.230
calculate it in any simple way.
 

00:50:43.230 --> 00:50:46.233
You can, again,
take a Gaussian surface and

00:50:46.233 --> 00:50:50.382
it'll still be true that the
integral of the electric field

00:50:50.382 --> 00:50:54.172
on that surface will be the same
Q/ε

00:50:54.172 --> 00:50:58.108
_0,
but the problem is the E

00:50:58.108 --> 00:51:00.829
on the surface is no longer
constant.

00:51:00.829 --> 00:51:01.610
You understand?
 

00:51:01.610 --> 00:51:04.260
Not every point is symmetric
any more.

00:51:04.260 --> 00:51:06.420
E may be stronger where
there's a bulge.

00:51:06.420 --> 00:51:08.666
E may be weaker where
there is hole,

00:51:08.666 --> 00:51:11.610
so and also its direction is
changing in a crazy way.

00:51:11.610 --> 00:51:13.971
So you can make one true
statement about the integral of

00:51:13.971 --> 00:51:15.860
that crazy function over the
whole region.

00:51:15.860 --> 00:51:20.376
That cannot be used to deduce
the value of E at every

00:51:20.376 --> 00:51:20.989
point.
 

00:51:20.989 --> 00:51:22.610
So you still need the integral.
 

00:51:22.610 --> 00:51:25.059
You may have to do the integral
maybe on a computer,

00:51:25.059 --> 00:51:26.780
but that's the answer to all
problems,

00:51:26.780 --> 00:51:32.331
but for simple problems with a
great deal of symmetry we can

00:51:32.331 --> 00:51:37.130
use Gauss's Law to get these
things very easily,

00:51:37.130 --> 00:51:38.670
okay?
 

00:51:38.670 --> 00:51:42.570
That's the Gauss.
 

00:51:42.570 --> 00:51:46.221
Now, I'm going to introduce you
to a second notion which is

00:51:46.221 --> 00:51:49.494
pretty important to study
electricity, and that's the

00:51:49.494 --> 00:51:51.070
notion of conductors.
 

00:51:51.070 --> 00:51:54.960
So we're going to divide the
world into two things,

00:51:54.960 --> 00:51:57.139
conductors and insulators.
 

00:51:57.139 --> 00:51:59.648
As you know,
matter is made up of positive

00:51:59.648 --> 00:52:03.012
and negative charges and the
negative charges circle the

00:52:03.012 --> 00:52:05.983
positive charges,
and they pretty much stay near

00:52:05.983 --> 00:52:09.557
their parent atoms,
near the parent nuclei,

00:52:09.557 --> 00:52:12.739
and you cannot separate them.
 

00:52:12.739 --> 00:52:17.443
But in a metal at least some of
the electrons from each atom

00:52:17.443 --> 00:52:18.880
become communal.
 

00:52:18.880 --> 00:52:21.967
In other words,
they can run around the whole

00:52:21.967 --> 00:52:22.530
solid.
 

00:52:22.530 --> 00:52:25.769
They don't belong to any one
nucleus.

00:52:25.769 --> 00:52:26.719
So that's a conductor.
 

00:52:26.719 --> 00:52:30.853
In a conductor the negative
charges, if you like,

00:52:30.853 --> 00:52:32.489
are free to move.
 

00:52:32.489 --> 00:52:41.150
So here's the first result.
 

00:52:41.150 --> 00:52:46.480
E is equal to 0 inside a
conductor.

00:52:46.480 --> 00:52:51.130
That really follows from the
meaning of the word conductor.

00:52:51.130 --> 00:52:54.110
If you took a chunk of perfect
conductor, maybe copper is good

00:52:54.110 --> 00:52:57.141
enough;
they'll be no electric field

00:52:57.141 --> 00:52:58.530
inside copper.
 

00:52:58.530 --> 00:52:59.670
Why?
 

00:52:59.670 --> 00:53:02.780
Because if this is the chunk of
material,

00:53:02.780 --> 00:53:05.652
this electric field,
then the charges that I said

00:53:05.652 --> 00:53:09.362
are free to move will respond to
the electric field and they'll

00:53:09.362 --> 00:53:10.199
be moving.
 

00:53:10.199 --> 00:53:15.367
So I should say E equal
to 0 inside a conductor in a

00:53:15.367 --> 00:53:17.059
static situation.
 

00:53:17.059 --> 00:53:20.702
In other words,
once the charges have stopped

00:53:20.702 --> 00:53:25.090
moving the electric field will
be 0 in a conductor.

00:53:25.090 --> 00:53:28.824
Let me explain to you a little
more what's going on so it's not

00:53:28.824 --> 00:53:29.789
a big mystery.
 

00:53:29.789 --> 00:53:36.717
Suppose there is a uniform
electric field going from left

00:53:36.717 --> 00:53:38.079
to right?
 

00:53:38.079 --> 00:53:42.740
In that uniform field I take a
chunk of copper like a nice

00:53:42.740 --> 00:53:46.340
rectangular chunk and I stick it
in there.

00:53:46.340 --> 00:53:49.179
What will happen?
 

00:53:49.179 --> 00:53:52.784
In the beginning the electric
field will penetrate the copper

00:53:52.784 --> 00:53:55.849
and the field lines say to the
positive charges,

00:53:55.849 --> 00:53:57.692
"You go to the
right," and to the negative

00:53:57.692 --> 00:53:59.969
charges,
"You go to the left."

00:53:59.969 --> 00:54:03.425
Negative charges will race to
the left until they cannot go

00:54:03.425 --> 00:54:05.630
anymore without leaving the
solid,

00:54:05.630 --> 00:54:07.480
and that they're not allowed to
do,

00:54:07.480 --> 00:54:13.519
leaving behind some deficit on
the other side.

00:54:13.519 --> 00:54:15.250
But look what's happening now.
 

00:54:15.250 --> 00:54:20.875
These guys produce their own
electric field which goes from

00:54:20.875 --> 00:54:22.329
here to here.
 

00:54:22.329 --> 00:54:25.219
Therefore, inside the
conductor, the electric field by

00:54:25.219 --> 00:54:28.217
the superposition principle is
the field due to whatever

00:54:28.217 --> 00:54:30.400
outside agency produced this
field,

00:54:30.400 --> 00:54:34.952
plus the field due to these
guys, and they will not stop

00:54:34.952 --> 00:54:39.672
until the field they produced
exactly cancels the external

00:54:39.672 --> 00:54:40.500
field.
 

00:54:40.500 --> 00:54:44.610
Then the migration will stop.
 

00:54:44.610 --> 00:54:46.289
So how do they know when to
stop?

00:54:46.289 --> 00:54:47.599
They are not that smart, right?
 

00:54:47.599 --> 00:54:51.239
But the point is once they've
produced the potential,

00:54:51.239 --> 00:54:55.088
I mean, once they produce the
field that cancels the external

00:54:55.088 --> 00:54:58.552
field there'll be no field
inside the bulk to encourage

00:54:58.552 --> 00:55:02.530
charges to move any more and
that's when they stop moving.

00:55:02.530 --> 00:55:05.030
Okay, so a conductor,
at least in this case,

00:55:05.030 --> 00:55:07.880
not so hard to understand what
they have to do.

00:55:07.880 --> 00:55:09.170
Negative charges go to one side.
 

00:55:09.170 --> 00:55:13.168
Positive go to the other side
until the field they produce is

00:55:13.168 --> 00:55:17.099
an arrow going to the left of
the same magnitude as this one

00:55:17.099 --> 00:55:19.099
then E is 0 inside.
 

00:55:19.099 --> 00:55:25.007
But what's amazing about these
metals is that if you take a

00:55:25.007 --> 00:55:30.509
potato shaped metal it's not so
easy to see what charge

00:55:30.509 --> 00:55:36.110
arrangement will exactly
neutralize the field everywhere

00:55:36.110 --> 00:55:37.639
in sight.
 

00:55:37.639 --> 00:55:38.679
Here it's easy to see.
 

00:55:38.679 --> 00:55:41.829
I want a right moving one
canceled with a left moving one.

